  "summary": "The next morning in the city of the Crow, Xiang Yue wakes up after a restless night to find his room empty. Wakatsuki has already departed for Kyoto, leaving Xiang Yue alone in a spacious, soundproof room with cold breakfast. While listening to Schubert on the radio, Xiang Yue reflects on the psychological effects of sensory deprivation.\n\nA loud, persistent knocking at the door leads Xiang Yue to discover two identical, beautiful girls: Miyuki and Kanae. Although Mutsu previously stated they were approximately twenty years old, they appear to be fifteen or sixteen, dressed in matching pink outfits with frilly aprons and flowered hats. They possess a youthful, innocent aura and gray eyes that show no emotion regarding the deaths of their father and grandfather.\n\nThe twins interact with Xiang Yue in a synchronized, \"stereo\" fashion that he finds physically difficult to endure. After a brief misunderstanding regarding his name, the girls ask if he has found the killer of their father and grandfather. Xiang Yue admits he has not, noting their unsettling lack of grief. The conversation turns to the identity of the killer; one girl suggests their great-grandfather is responsible, leading to a heated argument between the sisters. The encounter concludes with the two girls engaging in a physical shoving match in front of a stunned Xiang Yue.",
